APPENDIX B: ECONOMIC MODELS

B1: Discounted Cash Flow Analysis for Lunar Propellant Depot

Base Case Assumptions

Capital Expenditure (Year 0-5):

· Development & prototyping: $2.0B
· Launch costs (100 flights @ $50M): $5.0B
· Orbital construction robots: $3.0B
· Depot infrastructure: $4.0B
· Contingency (30%): $4.2B
· Total CapEx: $18.2B

Operational Parameters:

· Location: NRHO (Near Rectilinear Halo Orbit)
· Capacity: 2,000 tons LH2/LOX annually
· Utilization rate: Year 1-3: 30%, Year 4-6: 60%, Year 7+: 85%
· Price: $500/kg (vs. $2,000/kg from Earth)
· OpEx: $200M/year fixed + $50/kg variable

Financial Projections

Year Production (tons) Revenue ($M) OpEx ($M) EBITDA ($M) CAPEX ($M) Free Cash Flow ($M)
1-5 0 0 100 -100 3,640 -3,740
6 600 300 230 70 500 -430
7 1,200 600 260 340 200 140
8 1,700 850 285 565 100 465
9 2,000 1,000 300 700 50 650
10-20 2,000 1,000 300 700 50 650

Valuation Metrics

Discount Rate Analysis:

· Risk-free rate: 3%
· Equity risk premium: 6%
· Specific risk premium: 9%
· WACC: 18% (high frontier risk)

NPV Calculation:

· NPV @ 18%: -$2.1B (negative but strategic)
· NPV @ 12% (government strategic rate): +$3.8B
· NPV @ 8% (public benefit rate): +$12.4B

Break-even Analysis:

· At $600/kg: Breakeven Year 9
· At 85% utilization: Breakeven Year 8
· With 50% government subsidy: Breakeven Year 7

IRR Scenarios:

· Base case: 14.2%
· Optimistic ($600/kg, 90% util): 22.7%
· With carbon credits ($50/ton CO₂ avoided): +3.1% IRR

