B2: Comparative Cost/KWh: SBSP vs. Terrestrial Renewables + Storage (2040 Projection)

Methodology

Levelized Cost of Energy (LCOE) calculated per NREL methodology:

```
LCOE = (CapEx + ∑ OpEx/(1+r)^t) / (∑ Energy/(1+r)^t)
```

Where r = discount rate (7% for utility)

SBSP System (2 GW Capacity)

Capital Costs:

· Space segment: $12B ($6/W)
  · Solar arrays: $4B
  · Transmission: $5B
  · Assembly/Launch: $3B
· Ground segment: $2B ($1/W)
· Total: $14B ($7/W)

Operational Parameters:

· Capacity factor: 92%
· Annual output: 16.1 TWh
· Lifetime: 30 years
· OpEx: 1.5% of CapEx/year = $210M
· Decommissioning cost: 10% of CapEx = $1.4B

LCOE Calculation:

· Without transmission losses: $0.082/kWh
· With 5% terrestrial grid upgrade: $0.086/kWh
· 2040 Projection with learning curve (15% reduction): $0.073/kWh

Comparative Systems (2040)

Technology CapEx ($/W) Capacity Factor Storage Cost ($/kWh) LCOE ($/kWh)
SBSP 7.00 92% 0 0.073
Nuclear (Gen IV) 8.50 92% 0 0.095
Coal + CCS 6.50 85% 0 0.112
Solar PV + 8h Storage 1.20 25% 80 0.068
Wind + 8h Storage 2.10 45% 80 0.062
Geothermal 4.50 90% 0 0.078

Grid Value Analysis

Capacity Credit (Ability to meet peak demand):

· SBSP: 95% (baseload equivalent)
· Solar PV: 25%
· Wind: 40%

Integration Costs:

· SBSP: $5/MWh (grid stability)
· Solar PV: $15/MWh (curtailment, backup)
· Wind: $12/MWh

Adjusted LCOE with Grid Value:

· SBSP: $0.078/kWh
· Solar PV + Storage: $0.083/kWh
· Wind + Storage: $0.074/kWh

Sensitivity Analysis

Key Variables Impact on SBSP LCOE:

· Launch cost: ±$100/kg → ±$0.012/kWh
· Photovoltaic efficiency: ±5% → ±$0.008/kWh
· Discount rate: ±2% → ±$0.015/kWh
· Operating life: ±5 years → ±$0.010/kWh

