B3: Asteroid Mining: NPV Model for a Metallic NEA

Target Asteroid Profile

16 Psyche (Example metallic NEA):

· Diameter: 226 km
· Mass: 2.4×10¹⁹ kg
· Composition: 90% metal (Fe, Ni), 10% silicate
· Metal content: 2.2×10¹⁹ kg
· PGM concentration: 50 ppm (est.)
· PGM content: 1.1×10¹² kg (1,100 million tons)

Mining Reference Target (Smaller NEA):

· Diameter: 100 m
· Mass: 2.1×10⁹ kg (2.1 million tons)
· Metal: 80% = 1.68×10⁹ kg
· PGM: 100 ppm = 168,000 kg (168 tons @ $30,000/kg = $5B)
· Base metals: 1.68×10⁹ kg @ $2/kg = $3.4B
· Total in-situ value: $8.4B

Mission Architecture & Costs

Phase 1: Prospecting (Years 1-5)

· 2 robotic probes: $800M each
· Total: $1.6B

Phase 2: Extraction & Processing (Years 6-10)

· Mining spacecraft: $4B
· Processing plant: $3B
· Tug propulsion: $2B
· Total: $9B

Phase 3: Operations (Years 11-30)

· Annual OpEx: $400M
· Return flights (every 2 years): $300M/flight
· Total 20-year OpEx: $8B (PV)

Revenue Model

Production Schedule:

· Year 6-10: 10 tons PGMs/year + 10,000 tons base metals
· Year 11-20: 20 tons PGMs/year + 20,000 tons base metals
· Year 21-30: 30 tons PGMs/year + 30,000 tons base metals

Price Assumptions:

· PGMs: Start $30,000/kg, declining 5%/year due to increased supply
· Base metals: $2/kg constant
· Orbital delivery premium: 50% over terrestrial prices

Financial Analysis

Cash Flow Projection (Selected Years):

Year PGMs (tons) Revenue ($M) CapEx ($M) OpEx ($M) Net Cash ($M)
1-5 0 0 1,600 200 -1,800
6 10 285 3,000 500 -3,215
10 10 232 500 400 -168
15 20 354 0 400 -46
20 20 269 0 400 -131
25 30 305 0 400 -95
30 30 231 0 400 -169

Valuation Metrics:

· Total CapEx: $11.1B
· Total Revenue (30 years): $15.4B
· NPV @ 15% discount rate: -$4.2B
· IRR: 8.7%

Breakeven Conditions:

· PGM price: $40,000/kg → IRR 12.5%
· Production rate: 40 tons/year → IRR 11.8%
· CapEx reduction 30% → IRR 11.2%
· Combined improvements: IRR 15-20% achievable

Risk Analysis

Technical Risks (Probability × Impact):

· Asteroid characterization error (20% × $2B) = $400M
· Mining system failure (15% × $4B) = $600M
· Processing efficiency shortfall (25% × $1B) = $250M

Market Risks:

· PGM price collapse: -50% price → IRR 2.1%
· Terrestrial substitution: 10% probability
· Regulatory changes: 15% probability of delay

Risk-adjusted NPV:

· Expected NPV: -$4.2B
· Risk premium: +3% discount rate
· Risk-adjusted NPV: -$5.1B

Strategic Value Considerations

Non-Monetary Benefits:

· Technology development spinoffs: $2-4B value
· Space infrastructure created: $3-5B asset value
· Strategic metal independence: $1-2B national security value
· Total strategic value offset: $6-11B

Option Value:

· First-mover advantage in asteroid mining
· Claim to future mining rights
· Technology licensing potential
· Real option value: $2-3B

Adjusted Economic Case:

· Base NPV: -$4.2B
· · Strategic value: +$8.5B (midpoint)
· · Option value: +$2.5B
· = Strategic NPV: +$6.8B

