#### B1.3 Revenue Model

**Pricing Strategy:**

```
Lunar Propellant Pricing:
  - Cost from Earth (Falcon Heavy): $2,500/kg to LEO
  - Additional to GEO: +$1,500/kg (high-energy kick stage)
  - Total Earth-sourced propellant to GEO: $4,000/kg
  
  - Cost from Moon: $500/kg (target competitive price)
  - Lunar discount: 87.5% vs. Earth sourcing
  
Market Positioning:
  - Premium over cost ($33/kg variable + amortized fixed): Significant
  - Discount vs. alternatives: Compelling
  - Elasticity: High demand expected (enables new missions)
```

**Market Size Projection:**

| Customer Segment | Annual Demand (tons) | Notes |
|------------------|----------------------|-------|
| **Lunar surface missions** | 400 | Landers, rovers, return vehicles (2030s-2040s growth) |
| **Mars transfers** | 600 | Lunar orbit departure more efficient than LEO |
| **GEO satellite servicing** | 300 | Life extension, repositioning |
| **Deep space missions** | 200 | Science probes, asteroid missions |
| **Cislunar tourism** | 100 | Emerging market (lunar orbit hotels, surface visits) |
| **Defense/national security** | 200 | Classified missions; guaranteed offtake |
| **Total Addressable Market** | **1,800 tons/year** | By 2040 |

**Revenue Projection:**

| Year | Production (tons) | Price ($/kg) | Revenue | Notes |
|------|-------------------|--------------|---------|-------|
| 8 | 600 | $550 | $330M | Early market; premium pricing |
| 9 | 900 | $530 | $477M | Competitive entry; slight price reduction |
| 10 | 1,200 | $510 | $612M | Market expansion |
| 11-15 | 1,500 | $500 | $750M | Mature market; stable pricing |
| 16-27 | 1,700 | $500 | $850M | Full utilization; possible expansion |

